author: IGN
description:
Watch the Commandos: Origins – Shadows Over Crete launch trailer to learn more about this DLC, where you support the Cretan resistance in a new campaign with four missions. The new DLC for the real-time strategy game also brings the new Paratrooper enemy unit and new locations to navigate. Commandos: Origins – Shadows Over Crete DLC is out now on PC (Steam, Epic Games), Xbox Series X|S, Xbox on PC, Xbox One, PlayStation 4 (PS4), and PlayStation 5 (PS5).

In the new DLC, the Commandos unit steps behind enemy lines after the German invasion of Crete in May 1941 and help the fearless Cretan resistance, led by the fierce and loyal Eleni Andris. In a thrilling four-mission campaign of sabotage, espionage, and guerrilla warfare, the Green Beret and his team face the cunning new German Paratrooper as a new enemy unit, navigate through coastal villages, ancient ruins, and fortified islands, and test their stealth and strategy like never before.
title: Commandos: Origins – Shadows over Crete - Official Launch Trailer

author: IGN
description:
Project Motor Racing reviewed by Luke Reilly on PlayStation 5. Also availabe on Xbox Series X|S and PC.

"Right now, Project Motor Racing feels like an early access game that hasn’t actually been identified as such. There are certainly glimpses of a competent racing sim here, but it is drastically unfinished. With time, and its mod browser, I sincerely hope PMR can be fashioned into something that can fill the void left by the long-delisted Project CARS 2, but it's an entirely mediocre single-player racing experience for now. It may have positioned itself as the heir to the Project CARS 2 kingdom, but it is simply not a better racer than its 2017 ancestor."
title: Project Motor Racing Review

description:

Hoppers stars Piper Curda, Bobby Moynihan, Jon Hamm, Meryl Streep, Dave Franco, Kathy Najimy, Eduardo Franco, Melissa Villaseñor, Ego Nwodim, Vanessa Bayer, Sam Richardson, Aparna Nancherla, Nichole Sakura, Isiah Whitlock Jr., Steve Purcell, Karen Huie, and Tom Law.
